[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":792},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fcss\u002F2020\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fcss-design-patterns-oocss\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fcss\u002F2020\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fcss-design-patterns-oocss\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fcss\u002F2020\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fcss-design-patterns-oocss\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fcss\u002F2020\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fcss-design-patterns-oocss\u002F":768,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fcss\u002F2020\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fcss-design-patterns-oocss\u002F":777},"\u002Fcss\u002F20200517\u002F168089779\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":752,"date":753,"description":754,"extension":755,"lang":756,"meta":757,"navigation":331,"path":758,"readingMinutes":759,"seo":760,"standalone":761,"stem":762,"tags":763,"tldr":765,"updated":753,"url":766,"__hash__":767},"content\u002Fen\u002FCSS\u002Fcss-design-patterns-oocss.md","CSS Design Patterns — OOCSS","2227418287",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":745},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,37,40,43,85,88,91,94,264,287,393,399,419,422,425,428,431,494,497,571,589,602,723,726,730,741],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"OOCSS is another CSS design pattern. The biggest framework using it is Bootstrap.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"oocss","OOCSS",[17,25,26],{},"OOCSS stands for \"Object Oriented CSS\". The two core principles:",[28,29,30,34],"ul",{},[31,32,33],"li",{},"Separation of content from container",[31,35,36],{},"Separation of structure from skin",[17,38,39],{},"These two ideas massively improve CSS extensibility and flexibility. If you've used Bootstrap, you've already been doing OOCSS without realising — Bootstrap is built on OOCSS, where each class can stand on its own.",[17,41,42],{},"Example — you don't need to know CSS, just read the docs, and you can apply Bootstrap styles:",[44,45,50],"pre",{"className":46,"code":47,"language":48,"meta":49,"style":49},"language-html shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","\u003Ch1 class=\"text-left text-danger d-flex\">This is an h1\u003C\u002Fh1>\n","html","",[51,52,53],"code",{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,55,58,62,66,70,73,77,80,82],"span",{"class":56,"line":57},"line",1,[54,59,61],{"class":60},"s8XSl","\u003C",[54,63,65],{"class":64},"syv7_","h1",[54,67,69],{"class":68},"sK3KL"," class",[54,71,72],{"class":60},"=",[54,74,76],{"class":75},"sWayO","\"text-left text-danger d-flex\"",[54,78,79],{"class":60},">This is an h1\u003C\u002F",[54,81,65],{"class":64},[54,83,84],{"class":60},">\n",[17,86,87],{},"In OOCSS, each class is a self-contained CSS unit. This is similar to SMACSS's Module concept.",[12,89,33],{"id":90},"separation-of-content-from-container",[17,92,93],{},"The key idea — don't get locked into a specific layout. What does that look like?",[44,95,99],{"className":96,"code":97,"language":98,"meta":49,"style":49},"language-scss shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast",".header {\n  color: yellow;\n  width: 50px;\n  height: 50px;\n}\n.content {\n  color: red;\n  width: 50px;\n  height: 50px;\n}\n.footer {\n  color: blue;\n  width: 50px;\n  height: 50px;\n}\n","scss",[51,100,101,109,125,142,156,162,170,182,195,208,213,221,233,246,259],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,102,103,106],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,104,105],{"class":68},".header",[54,107,108],{"class":60}," {\n",[54,110,112,116,119,122],{"class":56,"line":111},2,[54,113,115],{"class":114},"stw71","  color",[54,117,118],{"class":60},": ",[54,120,121],{"class":114},"yellow",[54,123,124],{"class":60},";\n",[54,126,128,131,133,136,140],{"class":56,"line":127},3,[54,129,130],{"class":114},"  width",[54,132,118],{"class":60},[54,134,135],{"class":114},"50",[54,137,139],{"class":138},"sOudu","px",[54,141,124],{"class":60},[54,143,145,148,150,152,154],{"class":56,"line":144},4,[54,146,147],{"class":114},"  height",[54,149,118],{"class":60},[54,151,135],{"class":114},[54,153,139],{"class":138},[54,155,124],{"class":60},[54,157,159],{"class":56,"line":158},5,[54,160,161],{"class":60},"}\n",[54,163,165,168],{"class":56,"line":164},6,[54,166,167],{"class":68},".content",[54,169,108],{"class":60},[54,171,173,175,177,180],{"class":56,"line":172},7,[54,174,115],{"class":114},[54,176,118],{"class":60},[54,178,179],{"class":114},"red",[54,181,124],{"class":60},[54,183,185,187,189,191,193],{"class":56,"line":184},8,[54,186,130],{"class":114},[54,188,118],{"class":60},[54,190,135],{"class":114},[54,192,139],{"class":138},[54,194,124],{"class":60},[54,196,198,200,202,204,206],{"class":56,"line":197},9,[54,199,147],{"class":114},[54,201,118],{"class":60},[54,203,135],{"class":114},[54,205,139],{"class":138},[54,207,124],{"class":60},[54,209,211],{"class":56,"line":210},10,[54,212,161],{"class":60},[54,214,216,219],{"class":56,"line":215},11,[54,217,218],{"class":68},".footer",[54,220,108],{"class":60},[54,222,224,226,228,231],{"class":56,"line":223},12,[54,225,115],{"class":114},[54,227,118],{"class":60},[54,229,230],{"class":114},"blue",[54,232,124],{"class":60},[54,234,236,238,240,242,244],{"class":56,"line":235},13,[54,237,130],{"class":114},[54,239,118],{"class":60},[54,241,135],{"class":114},[54,243,139],{"class":138},[54,245,124],{"class":60},[54,247,249,251,253,255,257],{"class":56,"line":248},14,[54,250,147],{"class":114},[54,252,118],{"class":60},[54,254,135],{"class":114},[54,256,139],{"class":138},[54,258,124],{"class":60},[54,260,262],{"class":56,"line":261},15,[54,263,161],{"class":60},[17,265,266,268,269,268,271,273,274,277,278,281,282,277,284,286],{},[51,267,105],{},", ",[51,270,167],{},[51,272,218],{}," all share the same ",[51,275,276],{},"width"," and ",[51,279,280],{},"height",". If you use this pattern in 100 places, you're writing ",[51,283,276],{},[51,285,280],{}," 100 times — and changing the width means updating 100 places. The fix:",[44,288,290],{"className":96,"code":289,"language":98,"meta":49,"style":49},".container {\n  width: 50px;\n  height: 50px;\n}\n\n.header {\n  color: yellow;\n}\n.content {\n  color: red;\n}\n.footer {\n  color: blue;\n}\n",[51,291,292,299,311,323,327,333,339,349,353,359,369,373,379,389],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,293,294,297],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,295,296],{"class":68},".container",[54,298,108],{"class":60},[54,300,301,303,305,307,309],{"class":56,"line":111},[54,302,130],{"class":114},[54,304,118],{"class":60},[54,306,135],{"class":114},[54,308,139],{"class":138},[54,310,124],{"class":60},[54,312,313,315,317,319,321],{"class":56,"line":127},[54,314,147],{"class":114},[54,316,118],{"class":60},[54,318,135],{"class":114},[54,320,139],{"class":138},[54,322,124],{"class":60},[54,324,325],{"class":56,"line":144},[54,326,161],{"class":60},[54,328,329],{"class":56,"line":158},[54,330,332],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":331},true,"\n",[54,334,335,337],{"class":56,"line":164},[54,336,105],{"class":68},[54,338,108],{"class":60},[54,340,341,343,345,347],{"class":56,"line":172},[54,342,115],{"class":114},[54,344,118],{"class":60},[54,346,121],{"class":114},[54,348,124],{"class":60},[54,350,351],{"class":56,"line":184},[54,352,161],{"class":60},[54,354,355,357],{"class":56,"line":197},[54,356,167],{"class":68},[54,358,108],{"class":60},[54,360,361,363,365,367],{"class":56,"line":210},[54,362,115],{"class":114},[54,364,118],{"class":60},[54,366,179],{"class":114},[54,368,124],{"class":60},[54,370,371],{"class":56,"line":215},[54,372,161],{"class":60},[54,374,375,377],{"class":56,"line":223},[54,376,218],{"class":68},[54,378,108],{"class":60},[54,380,381,383,385,387],{"class":56,"line":235},[54,382,115],{"class":114},[54,384,118],{"class":60},[54,386,230],{"class":114},[54,388,124],{"class":60},[54,390,391],{"class":56,"line":248},[54,392,161],{"class":60},[17,394,395,396,398],{},"Now you can use ",[51,397,296],{}," directly in your HTML wherever you need that shape.",[17,400,401,402,268,404,268,407,410,411,414,415,418],{},"Real-world example — Bootstrap's grid system (",[51,403,296],{},[51,405,406],{},".row",[51,408,409],{},".col",") is \"container separation\". Content like ",[51,412,413],{},"ul>li"," or pagination can sit inside any of those containers — header, footer, wherever. If you write ",[51,416,417],{},".header ul li",", your CSS is locked into the header and can't be reused elsewhere.",[17,420,421],{},"In plain English — \"content should be reusable inside any container; avoid hard-coding content inside a specific container.\"",[12,423,36],{"id":424},"separation-of-structure-from-skin",[17,426,427],{},"The core idea — extract shared base styles, then make visual style a separate, reusable layer.",[17,429,430],{},"Wait, isn't this just SMACSS Module? Pretty close — but OOCSS focuses purely on one thing: if it's visual style, it's its own class. Example:",[44,432,434],{"className":96,"code":433,"language":98,"meta":49,"style":49},".btn {\n  width: 20px;\n  height: 100px;\n  color: red;\n  background-color: red;\n}\n",[51,435,436,443,456,469,479,490],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,437,438,441],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,439,440],{"class":68},".btn",[54,442,108],{"class":60},[54,444,445,447,449,452,454],{"class":56,"line":111},[54,446,130],{"class":114},[54,448,118],{"class":60},[54,450,451],{"class":114},"20",[54,453,139],{"class":138},[54,455,124],{"class":60},[54,457,458,460,462,465,467],{"class":56,"line":127},[54,459,147],{"class":114},[54,461,118],{"class":60},[54,463,464],{"class":114},"100",[54,466,139],{"class":138},[54,468,124],{"class":60},[54,470,471,473,475,477],{"class":56,"line":144},[54,472,115],{"class":114},[54,474,118],{"class":60},[54,476,179],{"class":114},[54,478,124],{"class":60},[54,480,481,484,486,488],{"class":56,"line":158},[54,482,483],{"class":114},"  background-color",[54,485,118],{"class":60},[54,487,179],{"class":114},[54,489,124],{"class":60},[54,491,492],{"class":56,"line":164},[54,493,161],{"class":60},[17,495,496],{},"Extract the visual style:",[44,498,500],{"className":96,"code":499,"language":98,"meta":49,"style":49},".btn-red {\n  color: red;\n  background-color: red;\n}\n\n.btn {\n  width: 20px;\n  height: 100px;\n}\n",[51,501,502,509,519,529,533,537,543,555,567],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,503,504,507],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,505,506],{"class":68},".btn-red",[54,508,108],{"class":60},[54,510,511,513,515,517],{"class":56,"line":111},[54,512,115],{"class":114},[54,514,118],{"class":60},[54,516,179],{"class":114},[54,518,124],{"class":60},[54,520,521,523,525,527],{"class":56,"line":127},[54,522,483],{"class":114},[54,524,118],{"class":60},[54,526,179],{"class":114},[54,528,124],{"class":60},[54,530,531],{"class":56,"line":144},[54,532,161],{"class":60},[54,534,535],{"class":56,"line":158},[54,536,332],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":331},[54,538,539,541],{"class":56,"line":164},[54,540,440],{"class":68},[54,542,108],{"class":60},[54,544,545,547,549,551,553],{"class":56,"line":172},[54,546,130],{"class":114},[54,548,118],{"class":60},[54,550,451],{"class":114},[54,552,139],{"class":138},[54,554,124],{"class":60},[54,556,557,559,561,563,565],{"class":56,"line":184},[54,558,147],{"class":114},[54,560,118],{"class":60},[54,562,464],{"class":114},[54,564,139],{"class":138},[54,566,124],{"class":60},[54,568,569],{"class":56,"line":197},[54,570,161],{"class":60},[17,572,573,574,577,578,268,580,268,582,268,585,588],{},"Analogy — separating a house's structure from its appearance. To use it: ",[51,575,576],{},"btn btn-red",". You get reusable CSS with less duplication. Base structure usually means ",[51,579,276],{},[51,581,280],{},[51,583,584],{},"padding",[51,586,587],{},"margin",". Skin usually means text colour, background colour, shadow.",[17,590,591,592,268,594,268,596,268,599,601],{},"OOCSS also has the concept of utilities — tiny helpers for ",[51,593,584],{},[51,595,587],{},[51,597,598],{},"border",[51,600,276],{},", etc.:",[44,603,605],{"className":96,"code":604,"language":98,"meta":49,"style":49},".pt-5 {\n  padding-top: 5px;\n}\n\n.mt-5 {\n  margin-top: 5px;\n}\n\n.border-all {\n  border: 1px solid #000000;\n}\n\n.w-100 {\n  width: 100%;\n}\